degree of Standardized Test of English Proficiency

The Standardized Test of English Proficiency (STEP) does not award degrees. It is a standardized test used to assess English proficiency in non-native speakers. It may be required for admission to universities or as part of a job application process, but it does not confer a degree upon completion.
